<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--BoysBuried     08-30 0144</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Boys Buried,0148</SECOND>
<HEAD>Boy Dies When Sand Bank Collapses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JUNCTION CITY, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A sand bank collapsed while two boys
were playing by digging foxholes, killing one boy and injuring the
second, authorities said.
   Anthony Zeiger, 9, was completely buried under the sand Monday
afternoon and probably died of asphyxiation, said Geary County
Sheriff Bill Deppish.
   His 10-year-old friend, Travis Enders, was buried up to his head.
He was treated at a hospital and released.
   Deppish said Travis reported the pair had been buried for a
little more than two hours before other youngsters heard his shouts
for help.
   The accident occurred along an 8-foot-deep drainage ditch near
the Republican River, behind the trailer court where the boys lived.
   ``Because of the recent rains down there, it was probably a
little more unstable than normal,'' Deppish said. ``The top just
caved in.''
</TEXT>
