<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Pakistan-Crash     08-30 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Pakistan-Crash,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bus Plunges Off Mountain Road, 35 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAIDU SHARIF, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus drove off a mountain road and
plunged 500 feet into a ravine, killing 35 people, police said.
   The accident took place near the mountain village of Shahpur in
the Swat valley, 100 miles northwest of Islamabad, the capital,
police said.
   The bus was on a regular mountain run between the villages of
Alipuri to Alandar when it swerved on a sharp curve and plunged over
the edge.
   Police said 35 passengers died instantly, five others survived
with injuries. Their conditions were not immediately disclosed.
   Pakistan's northern areas have been soaked with monsoon rains
recently, but police said they did not know if weather was a factor
in the bus crash.
</TEXT>
