<HEAD>Exterminators Take Aim at City Hall</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAKE OZARK, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Exterminators began their attack on a
closed-down City Hall in their war to rid the building's basement of
rats, mice, fleas and squirrels.
   Building inspector Tom Harmon declared the building in this small
resort community unfit for humans Monday because of the rodent and
parasite population. The extermination began Tuesday.
   The building would remain closed until Thursday morning, Harmon
said.
   Lake Ozark Mayor Rick Moss said he saw the action as a positive
step toward cleaning up the city.
   ``And if that means shutting down City Hall, we're going to do
it,'' Moss said.
   In April, the city council passed a dangerous buildings ordinance
and hired Harmon as part-time inspector.
