<HEAD>Former EC Vice President Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lorenzo Natali, who served as vice president of the
European Commission for 11 years and helped negotiate the entry of
Spain, Portugal and Greece into the European Economic Community, has
died at the age of 66.
   Natali died Monday at his Rome residence following a long illness.
   He served on the commission, the executive body of the EEC, until
December.
   Natali, a Christian Democrat, was elected to the Italian Chamber
of Deputies at the age of 26 and served in 15 governments, with
stints as minister of merchant marine, public works, tourism and
agriculture.
