<FIRST>r a PM-EmergencyLanding 1stLd-Writethru a0590 08-30 0192</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Emergency Landing, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0590,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>American Airlines Jet Makes Emergency Landing</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS last graf to CORRECT spelling of McDonnell Douglas.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OKLAHOMA CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American Airlines jet made an emergency
landing at an airport today after one of its three hydraulic systems
failed, an airline spokesman said.
   Flight 891, carrying 66 passengers and a crew of six from
Oklahoma City to Dallas, returned to Will Rogers World Airport 11
minutes after taking off, said American spokesman Jim Brown.
   He said the loss of any one or two of the hydraulic systems would
not result in the pilot losing control of the airplane, as happened
with a DC-10 that crashed at Sioux City, Iowa, after losing all
three of its hydraulic systems.
   ``I want to emphasize this kind of airplane has a hydraulically
assisted flight control system. But even if all three (hydraulic
systems) went out ... there would be a cable system to pilot the
aircraft,'' Brown said.
   Brown said mechanics would inspect the plane, a McDonnell Douglas
MD80, to determine if it should be taken out of service and the
passengers transferred to other flights.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
