announced Wednesday it will hold four days of hearings in Sioux
City, Iowa, in its investigation of the crash of a United Airlines
plane at the Sioux City Airport.
   A board spokeswoman, Betty Scott, said the hearings would begin
Oct. 31 at the Sioux City convention center. She said a list of
