<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The director and several other officials of
Cuba's state railroad company were fired after an inquiry into a
crash that killed 52 people, the official Cuban news agency Prensa
Latina said Wednesday.
   Prensa Latina said the dismissals were ``meant to strengthen
