<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The reputed leader of the Medellin
cocaine cartel has threatened more violence if the government
refuses to make peace and allow drug traffickers to rejoin society,
according to a newspaper report.
   The government has rejected all calls for negotiations, however,
and a television report Tuesday said authorities were preparing to
