   A strong Hispanic turnout helped make Republican
Ileana Ros-Lehtinen the first Cuban-American elected to Congress,
ending an ethnically divisive campaign for the seat held by Democrat
Claude Pepper for 27 years.
   ``Now it's time to forget our differences and focus on unity. ...
we are all Americans,'' Ms. Ros-Lehtinen said after defeating
