<FIRST>a e BC-FallTV-MajorDad Adv01-03   08-30 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Fall TV-Major Dad, Adv 01-03,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>$Adv01-03</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Weekend Editions, Sept. 1-3, and Thereafter</HEAD>
<HEAD>`Major Dad' Wins Salute</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   CBS' ``Major Dad'' isn't uniformly funny _ pun
intended _ but it does deserve a salute.
   The bankable Gerald McRaney (``Simon &amp; Simon'') stars as Marine
Maj. J.D. ``Mac'' MacGillis. He has a simple Marine philosophy:
``See the hill, take the hill.'' That's how he manages to woo and
win a bride in one 30-minute pilot.
   She is Polly Cooper, a liberal-thinking newspaper reporter with
three daughters, and is played by newcomer Shanna Reed. The
chemistry between Reed and McRaney and the natural setting for comic
conflict bodes well for a long tour of duty.
   ``Major Dad'' has a tough assignment, leading off CBS' Monday
lineup of comedies. But as Mac says, ``See the hill, take the hill.''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sept. 1-3</NOTE>
