<DOCNO> AP890830-0225 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-08-30-89 0202EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-Digital-Aquarius     08-30 0156</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Digital-Aquarius,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Digital to Launch New Top-Of-The-Line Computers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Digital Equipment Corp. plans to introduce a new
line of computers this fall that Digital executives hope will give
the company an entry into the mainframe class of computers.
   Analysts said the range of top-of-the-line computers called Vax
9000, and code-named Aquarius, will compete with computers made by
International Business Machines Corp., Uisys Corp., Amdahl Corp.,
Tandem Computers Inc. and others.
   ``They're not quite betting the company on the product, but
they're betting substantial human and financial resources on it,''
said Terry C. Shannon, an analyst with International Data Corp. in
Framingham.
   Digital relies heavily on sales of minicomputers, but that market
is slumping. Wang Laboratories Inc., Data General Corp., Prime
Computer Inc. and others have also been affected by the slowdown.
   Digital's Vax 9000 line will have features that make it
well-suited for processing large numbers of transactions at high
speeds, analysts said.
</TEXT>
