<FIRST>r f AM-AtlanticRecords     08-30 0117</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Atlantic Records,0120</SECOND>
<HEAD>Atlantic Gives Morris Chief Operating Officer Title</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Doug Morris, the president of Atlantic Records,
was given the additional title of chief operating officer on
Wednesday, strengthening his position as heir apparent to Atlantic
Chairman and Chief Executive Ahmet M. Ertegun.
   Although he is 65, Ertegun said Wednesday he has no immediate
plans to retire from the company he founded in 1947. Atlantic
Records is part of Warner Communications Inc., which is being
acquired by Time Inc. to form Time Warner Inc.
   Morris, 50, already had day-to-day responsibility for Atlantic
operations, so the promotion is more of a recognition of his
achievements than a change of duties, company officials said.
</TEXT>
