<FIRST>r f AM-Schlumberger-NTT     08-30 0086</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Schlumberger-NTT,0090</SECOND>
<HEAD>Schlumberger, NTT Form Chip-Testing Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Schlumberger Ltd. of France and Japan's Nippon
Telegraph &amp; Telephone Corp. said Wednesday they had formed a
company, Verisys, to develop systems for testing the performance of
computer chips.
   The systems will test chips that are custom-made for certain
jobs, known as application-specific integrated circuits. Verisys
will be based in Japan and will include managerial and technical
people from both parents.
   Schlumberger will ensure the distribution and maintenance of
Verisys products, the companies said.
</TEXT>
