<HEAD>With AM-Helmsley Trial, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The following is the verdict brought Wednesday
against Leona Helmsley and her co-defendants, Frank Turco and Joseph
Licari:
   
   Count 1 _ Mrs. Helmsley, Turco and Licari, convicted of
conspiracy to defraud the Internal Revenue Service in 1983-85.
   Count 2 _ Mrs. Helmsley, convicted of tax evasion in 1983.
   Count 3 _ Mrs. Helmsley, convicted of tax evasion in 1984.
   Count 4 _ Mrs. Helmsley, convicted of tax evasion in 1985.
   Count 5 _ Licari and Turco, convicted of aiding and abetting tax
evasion in 1983.
   Count 6 _ Licari and Turco, convicted of aiding and abetting tax
evasion in 1984.
   Count 7 _ Licari and Turco, convicted of aiding and abetting tax
evasion in 1986.
   Count 8 _ Mrs. Helmsley, convicted of making and subscribing
false personal tax returns in 1983.
   Count 9 _ Mrs. Helmsley, convicted of making and subscribing
false personal tax returns in 1984.
   Count 10 _ Mrs. Helmsley, convicted of making and subscribing
false personal tax returns in 1985.
   Count 11 _ Licari and Turco, convicted of aiding and assisting
the filing of false personal tax returns in 1983.
   Count 12 _ Licari and Turco, convicted of aiding and assisting in
filing false personal tax returns in 1984.
   Count 13 _ Licari and Turco, convicted of aiding and assisting in
filing false personal tax returns in 1985.
   Counts 14-29 _ Mrs. Helmsley, Licari and Turco, convicted of
aiding and assisting in the filing of false returns for businesses
in the Helmsley organization.
   Counts 30-39 _ Mrs. Helmsley, Licari and Turco, convicted of mail
fraud as part of a scheme to defraud the state Department of
Taxation and Finance by filing false state income tax returns.
   Counts 40-46 _ Mrs. Helmsley, Licari and Turco, acquitted of mail
fraud as part of a scheme to defraud minority shareholders of a
Helmsley-controlled partnership.
   Count 47 _ Mrs. Helmsley and Turco, acquitted of extortion
conspiracy to get kickbacks from vendors.
